---
// Registers the Etus service worker after the page is interactive — PRODUCTION ONLY.
// SW source lives at /sw.js (emitted by src/pages/sw.js.ts).
// T1.5: extra drain triggers — Safari/Firefox don't have BackgroundSync, so the
// queue only drains when something signals the SW. We signal on: initial register,
// `online` event, `controllerchange` (new SW takes over), and (Chrome) periodic via sync.
//
// DEV: the SW is a footgun locally. HTML is served network-first with a 2s timeout
// that falls back to CACHED HTML; during a Vite recompile (often >2s) the SW serves
// the stale cached page (with stale inline CSS), so edits look "stale across reloads
// and even restarts". So in dev we DON'T register — and we actively UNREGISTER any
// existing SW + nuke its caches so local review always reflects the latest build.
//
// T11: the IIFE body (dev unregister + prod register/nudge) moved to
// src/lib/sw-register.ts, bundled as a hashed/cached /_astro/*.js module
// <script> instead of ~1.3 KB of inline JS per page. The dev/prod split lives
// inside that module (import.meta.env.DEV, statically replaced at build). Runs
// once on import — no data-astro-rerun needed.
---

<script>
  import '../lib/sw-register.ts';
</script>
